const handlePlayer1Select = (event) => {
  const selectedRk = event.target.value;
  const selectedPlayer = playerstatistics.find(player => player.Rk === selectedRk);
  setSelectedPlayer1(selectedPlayer);
};

const handlePlayer2Select = (event) => {
  const selectedRk = event.target.value;
  const selectedPlayer = playerstatistics.find(player => player.Rk === selectedRk);
  setSelectedPlayer2(selectedPlayer);
};

return (
  <div className="player-stats-page">
      <h1>Player Statistics</h1>
      <div className="player-select">
          <select className="player-select-input" onChange={handlePlayer1Select}>
              <option value="">Select Player 1</option>
              {playerstatistics.map(player => (
                  <option key={player.Rk} value={player.Rk}>{player.Player}</option>
              ))}
          </select>
          <select className="player-select-input" onChange={handlePlayer2Select}>
              <option value="">Select Player 2</option>
              {playerstatistics.map(player => (
                  <option key={player.Rk} value={player.Rk}>{player.Player}</option>
              ))}
          </select>
      </div>
      {selectedPlayer1 && selectedPlayer2 && (
          <Comparison player1={selectedPlayer1} player2={selectedPlayer2} />
      )}
  </div>
);
};
